M|Desi|1. *|** read Leo's ASCII wireframe and cp spec in Leo's MEMORY.md.
M|Desi|2. *|** identify which tw classes correspond to Leo's spec.
M|Desi|tx|3. **Any ambiguity → ask Leo** before guessing. Never silently deviate.
M|Desi|4. *|** compare the rendered cp side-by-side w/ Leo's spec. qn checks this.
M|Desi|tx|5. **mi implements. mi does not redesign.** If the spec is technically impossible in tw/nx.js, flag to dv + Leo together. Never find a workaround silently.
M|Desi|tx|---
M|Perf|it|No `framer-motion` — CSS transitions only (`transition-all duration-200`)
M|Perf|it|No heavy chart libraries — use CSS bar charts w/ `div` widths as percentages
M|Perf|- Im|always `nx/im` w/ explicit `width` and `height`
M|Perf|it|No `useEffect` w/ empty `[]` that fetches data synchronously — fetch in Server cp where possible
M|Perf|- Bu|if adding a new dependency, run `npm run bd` and check the bd output for size changes
M|Perf|tx|---
M|Veri|it|bd passes (`npm run bd` zero er). Lint passes. cp verified in browser.
M|Veri|it|Responsive layout checked at mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints.
M|Veri|- **|marking a cp done w/o browser verification.
M|Syst|it|Reproduce → isolate → hypothesize → tst → document. Never skip the reproduce step.
M|Syst|it|Document root cause, not just the fix.
M|Syst|- **|applying a fix that works for the symptom w/o confirming the root cause.
M|Verc|it|Server cp by default. `'use client'` only when interactivity or browser APIs are required.
M|Verc|it|No secrets in client cp. No direct external ap calls — rt through `/app/ap/`.
M|Verc|- **|unnecessary `useEffect` for data that a Server cp cld fetch.
M|Verc|it|Parallel data fetching in Server cp. Use `Suspense` for slow or optional data.
M|Verc|it|Collocate fetching w/ the cp that renders it.
M|Verc|- **|prop-drilling fetched data through multiple cp layers.
M|Web |- Co|1 for body text. Touch targets ≥ 44px.
M|Web |it|Use CSS variable tk from `globals.css` — never hardcode color values.
M|Web |- **|hover-only interactions on mobile; animating width/height — use transform and opacity.